  	<h1>Install server locally</h1>
  	<p>To control your presentation with Iphone you need a server. You can use <a href="http://remote.nodester.com">http://remote.nodester.com</a> but if you have slow connection, latency will kill awesomeness of your presentation. To prevent it you need to install server locally.</p>
  	</div>
  <div class="span6">
  	<h1>Windows</h1>
  	<ul>
  		<li>Download and install <a href="http://nodejs.org/dist/v0.6.11/node-v0.6.11.msi">node</a></li>
      <li>open terminal, install and run remote-impress
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">   $ npm install remote-impress -g
   $ remote-impress</pre>
   </li>
  	 <li>run <a href="http://localhost">http://localhost</a> in browser</li>
    </ul>
  	</div>  	
  </div>
